definition.value: A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate having adenine as the nucleobase.
A cholestanoid that is cholest-4-ene substituted by an oxo group at position 3.
The D-enantiomer of ornithine. It is an intermediate metabolite produced in the urea cycle.
A polymannosidic phosphodiester in which one secondary phosphoryl is linked as mannose 6-phosphate and the other as alpha-hemiacetal phosphate.
